  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>chicken breast portion[s]</strong> to a chopping board</p><p>Cover with <strong>cling film</strong> and bash with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> until flattened to approx. 1cm thickness</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1724066896228-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1724066896228-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1724066896228-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1724066896228-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1724066896228-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>flattened chicken</strong> to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 4 min on each side  then turn the heat down to medium and cook for a further 3-4 min or until browned and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? You may need to do this in batches!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1724066908044-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1724066908044-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1724066908044-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1724066908044-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1724066908044-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the chicken is cooking, trim your<strong> green beans</strong></p><p>Roughly chop your<strong> roasted</strong> <strong>peanuts</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> and shake off any excess water</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1724066917806-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1724066917806-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1724066917806-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1724066917806-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1724066917806-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>green beans</strong> to the pan and cook for 5-6 min or until lightly charred</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1724066930865-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1724066930865-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1724066930865-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1724066930865-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1724066930865-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> finely</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chopped creamed coconut</strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>red Thai curry paste</strong> and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>tamari soy sauce</strong> (you’ll use the rest later!) with a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and stir it all together – this is your <strong>red Thai curry stock</strong></p><p>Squeeze your pouch[es] of <strong>cooked brown long grain rice </strong>to separate the grains</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1724066939367-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
